## Edge Case Handling Summary

| Scenario | Handling |
|---|---|
| `@id Int @default(autoincrement())` | `isAutoGeneratedField` returns true → excluded from `CreateInput` |
| `@updatedAt DateTime` | `isUpdatedAt` is true → excluded from `CreateInput` |
| `isGenerated: true` field | Excluded from `CreateInput` |
| Optional/nullable scalar (`isRequired: false`) | Type becomes `T \| null`, field optional with `?:` |
| List field (`isList: true`) | Type becomes `T[]`, then nullable wrapper if needed |
| `kind: 'enum'` field | References the generated enum type alias by name |
| `kind: 'object'` relation in model interface | Optional field (the server may or may not include it) |
| `kind: 'object'` relation in CreateInput/UpdateInput | Skipped entirely (`fieldToTsType` returns `null`) |
| Composite `@@id` model | `getWhereUniqueFields` returns all `primaryKey.fields` |
| Model with no `@id` or `@@id` | Falls back to all `@unique` scalar fields |
| `kind: 'unsupported'` field | Type is `unknown` |
| `CamelCase` model name | `toKebabCase` converts to kebab-case for URL segments (e.g., `BlogPost` → `blog-post`) |
| Composite key in `findUnique`/`update`/`delete` URL | `extractId` serializes as `encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(where))` |
| Non-existent or deleted output dir | `generateRestClient` always does `rm -rf` then `mkdir -p` before writing |
| `BigInt` over JSON | Maps to `string` |
| `Decimal` over JSON | Maps to `string` |
| Fields with `hasDefaultValue: true` in `CreateInput` | Made optional via `?:` even if technically required in DB |

